# msgvault analytics

{{template "basics" .}}

## Built-in aggregates (try these first)

```bash
msgvault stats
msgvault stats --account you@gmail.com
msgvault list-accounts --json
msgvault list-senders --json -n 25 --after 2024-01-01 --before 2025-01-01
msgvault list-domains --json
msgvault list-labels --json
```

`list-senders`/`list-domains`/`list-labels` JSON rows are
`{key, count, total_size, attachment_size}`. `stats` is text-only
(no `--json`).

## Custom SQL

`query` runs read-only SQL (DuckDB syntax) over the Parquet analytics
cache:

```bash
msgvault query "SELECT from_domain, COUNT(*) AS n FROM v_messages WHERE year = 2024 GROUP BY 1 ORDER BY n DESC LIMIT 10"
msgvault query --format csv "SELECT * FROM v_senders ORDER BY message_count DESC LIMIT 20"
```

Default output is `--format json`:
`{"columns": [...], "rows": [[...]], "row_count": N}`. Also `csv` and
`table`.

### Convenience views

- `v_messages` — one row per message: `id`, `source_id`,
  `source_message_id`, `conversation_id`, `subject`, `snippet`,
  `sent_at`, `size_estimate`, `has_attachments`, `attachment_count`,
  `message_type`, `year`, `month`, `from_email`, `from_name`,
  `from_domain`, `from_phone`, `labels` (JSON array as string),
  `deleted_from_source_at`.
- `v_senders` — per sender: `from_email`, `from_name`, `from_domain`,
  `message_count`, `total_size`, `attachment_size`, `attachment_count`,
  `first_message_at`, `last_message_at`.
- `v_domains` — per sender domain: `domain`, `message_count`,
  `total_size`, `sender_count`.
- `v_labels` — per label: `name`, `message_count`, `total_size`.
- `v_threads` — per conversation: `conversation_id`,
  `source_conversation_id`, `conversation_title`, `conversation_type`,
  `message_count`, `first_message_at`, `last_message_at`,
  `participant_emails` (JSON array as string).

Base views for joins: `messages`, `participants`, `message_recipients`
(`recipient_type` ∈ from/to/cc/bcc), `labels`, `message_labels`,
`attachments` (`message_id`, `filename`, `size`), `conversations`,
`sources`.

### Notes

- Message bodies are not in the analytics cache; use
  `msgvault show-message <id> --json` for content.
- Analytics counts include messages already deleted from the source;
  filter with `WHERE deleted_from_source_at IS NULL` to match the
  active counts shown by `stats`.
- Time series: group by the `year` and `month` columns of `v_messages`.

